    <fields>
        <fullName>RC_Personal_Gain__c</fullName>
        <description>This refers to situations where you are a researcher, author or research supervisor who could receive direct or indirect personal benefit, including, but is not limited to a financial benefit, from or through:
- the outcome of clinical trials, biomedical or other research; 
- commercialisation, collaborations and relationships with industry in the licensing and marketing of research discoveries or teaching resources, including through the creation of a spin-off company or the creation of products or services; 
- providing exclusive access to University intellectual property without following procedures for the commercialisation of intellectual property; 
- as part of a sponsored research project or research activity, entering into a contract on behalf of the University with an outside entity in which they, an immediate family member or business partner/s has a financial interest either directly or through another related outside entity;
- assigning a student, trainee or postdoc</description>
